From: Regg819 <carlosoundman@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 2026 17:23:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(ci): add systematic spellcheck workflow
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add automated spellchecking to CI pipeline for improved code quality.

Changes:
- Add spellcheck_ci.py script with 150+ common typo patterns
- Add GitHub Actions workflow for automated checking
- Fix typo in comment: 'occured' → 'occurred' (quic.rs)

The spellcheck runs on:
- Push to master/main branches
- Pull requests
- Scans .rs, .md, .toml, .yaml, .json files

Note: Additional typos found in variable names (reciever → receiver)
are documented in refactoring-plan-reciever.md for future consideration.

See: anza-xyz/agave#7819
---
 .github/workflows/spellcheck.yml |  47 ++++
 scripts/spellcheck_ci.py         | 360 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 streamer/src/nonblocking/quic.rs |   2 +-
 3 files changed, 408 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100644 .github/workflows/spellcheck.yml
